    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "That's a great start for the intro. I've heard some legal scholars argue that focusing too much on 'substantive' due process can actually be problematic or that we should stick strictly to 'procedural' due process instead. How would you explain that perspective to the students so they understand why some people are skeptical of the substantive approach?",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
