      "content": "thanks for that. i'm trying to decide how to frame the conclusion of the lesson. i want my students to realize that while the skeptics have their points, the substantive due process approach is really the only way to ensure fundamental rights aren't just subject to the whims of whatever party is in power at the moment. do you think that's a fair way to wrap up the lesson, or is it too one-sided?",
